					<div class="leftnote"><span class="xar-sub">Posted:Jun 28, 2007 3:18:52 PM</span></div>
					<div class="rightnote">
											</div>
					<div style="float:left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject:<a name="86285" href="http://www.ldonline.org/xarbb/topic/14496#86285">Just wondering what other parents are doing this summer
</a></strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>I've always done &quot;homeschooling&quot; during the summer with my kids. Learning doesn't stop just because the school system says it should. Fun reading activities, computer reading programs, etc. We found that activities with lots of movement helped a lot. </p>
<p>This summer my dd is going to work on her algebra skills, learn chemistry and physics, read fun books and work on German Vocabulary. LOL (She's 15.)</p>
																		<p class="hiddensignature">scifinut
mom to: ms 16, bp/adhd/anxiety/complex ld
mr. 20, add/dyslexic

I hear and I forget
I see and I remember
I do and I understand.
-Anonymous</p>
															</div>
